<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"One-sample_t-test">One-samp=
le <i>t</i>-test</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-edits=
ection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?tit=
le=3DStudent%27s_t-test&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit se=
ction: One-sample t-test"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A <b>one-sample Student's <i>t</i>-test</b> is a <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Location_test" title=3D"Location test">location test</a> =
of whether the mean of a population has a value specified in a <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Null_hypothesis" title=3D"Null hypothesis">nul=
l hypothesis</a>. In testing the null hypothesis that the population mean i=
s equal to a specified value <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=CE=BC</i><sub>0</s=
ub></span>, one uses the statistic
</p>
