<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Calculations">Calculations<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DStudent%27s_=
t-test&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Calculatio=
ns"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></div>
<p>Explicit expressions that can be used to carry out various <i>t</i>-test=
s are given below. In each case, the formula for a test statistic that eith=
er exactly follows or closely approximates a <i>t</i>-distribution under th=
e null hypothesis is given. Also, the appropriate <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Degrees_of_freedom_(statistics)" title=3D"Degrees of freedo=
m (statistics)">degrees of freedom</a> are given in each case. Each of thes=
e statistics can be used to carry out either a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/One-tailed_test" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"One-tailed tes=
t">one-tailed or two-tailed test</a>.
