/span></div>
<p>This test is used when the samples are dependent; that is, when there is=
 only one sample that has been tested twice (repeated measures) or when the=
re are two samples that have been matched or "paired". This is an example o=
f a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paired_difference_test" title=
=3D"Paired difference test">paired difference test</a>. The <i>t</i> statis=
tic is calculated as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e t=3D{\frac {{\bar {X}}_{D}-\mu _{0}}{s_{D}/{\sqrt {n}}}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <msub>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mover>
                      <mi>X</mi>
                      <mo stretchy=3D"false">=C2=AF<!-- =C2=AF --></mo>
                    </mover>
                  </mrow>
                </mrow>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>D</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
