f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sample_covariance_matrix" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Sample covariance matrix">sample covariance matrix</a>.
</p><p>For a two-sample multivariate test, the hypothesis is that the mean =
vectors (<span class=3D"texhtml"><b>=CE=BC</b><sub>1</sub>, <b>=CE=BC</b><s=
ub>2</sub></span>) of two samples are equal. The test statistic is <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotelling%27s_two-sample_t-squared_statis=
tic" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hotelling's two-sample t-squared statis=
tic">Hotelling's two-sample <i>t</i><span style=3D"padding-left:0.12em;"><s=
up>2</sup></span></a>:
</p>
